You will see 3 folders.The "pages" folder is where the routing happens.That will direct the url page in your app.For example if you had a file called `contact-us.js` to be routed to it you would have the following url your browser `http://localhost:3000/contact-us`. This will show the content from that component.Your **pages** folder will have a **api** folder and two files `_app.js` and `index.js`.Open the project in a browser and you should see something like this

